  "label": "The Quiet Spline",
  "description": "The Quiet Spline functions as a compact bedroom carved into the Index Lantern’s pressure-rated shell, its walls sheathed in black composite scored with transit indices in fine conductor inlay. A berth recess and built-in storage are integrated flush to preserve clearance under Continuum Anchorage’s modular tolerances. Acoustic baffles and a gasketed threshold enforce isolation from the tavern’s partitioned seating bays, holding the room in a stable hush. Steady, low radiance from conductor-metal fixtures maintains the anchorage’s unvarying gloom without casting hard shadows.",
